==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymomlogy===
From [[Ancient Greek]] [[κινητικός]] "[[kinetic]]" + [[ενέργεια]] "[[energy]]".
===Noun phrase===
'''[[kinetic]] [[energy]]'''
#{{cattag|Physics}}: The energy possessed by an [[object]] because of its motion, equal to one half the mass of the body times the square of its speed.
